## What I Learned
This room introduced several penetration testing frameworks and highlighted the importance of following a structured methodology during security assessments.

Rather than focusing on individual tools, the room emphasized the different stages involved in a penetration test, from planning and reconnaissance to reporting findings.

## Key Takeaway
A successful penetration test relies on a repeatable and structured process. Methodology is just as important as technical skills and tools.
